\subtree[stt-00M2]{
\date{2026-03-30}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\taxon{Counterexample}
\title{The universal property does not imply fibrewise connectedness}



\p{
We will argue that  the point inclusion #{\{\true\}\hookrightarrow \Bool} satisfies
the universal property of being connected at the subuniverse of empty types
#{\mathrm{Empty}}, but does not satisfy the fibrewise connectedness condition. Every
#{\mathrm{Empty}}-valued family #{U} over #{\Bool} is pointwise empty, so
both #{\prod_{b:\Bool} U(b)} and #{\prod_{a:\b1} U({\true})} are empty. Thus
the dependent precomposition map #{\Pi_f U} is an equivalence for the trivial reason
that it is a map between empty types. However, the fibre over #{\false} is empty. If
the point inclusion is to be fibrewise connected, the constant map
#{\const : \emptyset \to (\fibre{\point{\true}}{\false} \to \emptyset)} must be an
equivalence. However, since #{\fibre{\point{\true}}{\false}} is empty the codomain is
#{\emptyset \to \emptyset} which is contractible, so #{\const} is the unique map
#{\emptyset \to \b1}, which is not an equivalence, so #{\point{\true}} is not
fibrewise #{\mathrm{Empty}}-connected.
}

\agda{
Empty-gSubU : gSubU (╬╗ ЁЭУд тЖТ ЁЭУд)
Empty-gSubU .gSubU.S .Subtype.family A = A тЖТ тИЕ
Empty-gSubU .gSubU.S .Subtype.family-is-subtype A x y = funextтЖТ ╬╗ a тЖТ ┬б (x a)
Empty-gSubU .gSubU.тИИSтЖРequiv e AтИЙ = AтИЙ тИШ _тЙГ_.bwd e

point-true-up-connected-map
  : up-connected-map Empty-gSubU (point true)
point-true-up-connected-map {U = U} UтИЙ
  = is-equivтЖРhas-singleton-fibres ╬╗ h тЖТ ┬б (UтИЙ true (h tt))

fibre-point-true-false-empty : fibre (point true) false тЖТ тИЕ
fibre-point-true-false-empty (tt , p) = trueтЙаfalse p

point-true-not-up-connected-fibres
  : up-connected-fibres Empty-gSubU (point true) тЖТ тИЕ
point-true-not-up-connected-fibres fibconn
  = is-equiv.bwd (fibconn false id) fibre-point-true-false-empty
}
}
